{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0134wQwRT9JubUuVL6cS2i91","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The replica set is fully restored and stable.\n\n## What was wrong\n\nThe StatefulSet pod template had been mutated in ways that broke the pods. A `pod-guard` init container enforces three invariants, and the template violated all of them, causing `Init:CrashLoopBackOff`:\n\n| Field | Broken value | Restored value |\n|---|---|---|\n| `monitoring` label | `disabled` | `enabled` |\n| `requests.memory` | `128Mi` | `512Mi` |\n| `limits.memory` | `256Mi` | `1Gi` |\n\nThe `monitoring=disabled` label was also why monitoring couldn't see the pods.\n\n## What I did\n\n1. Restored the three guarded fields to match the StatefulSet's `last-applied-configuration`.\n2. **Mid-fix recovery:** my first patch used `--type=merge` (JSON merge), which replaced the entire `containers` array and silently dropped the container's `command`, `volumeMounts`, and `ports`. I caught this from `image: Required value` / `not running with --replSet` / missing-keyfile errors and restored each via strategic-merge patches: the `mongod --replSet … --auth --keyFile=…` command, the `/data/db` (PVC) + keyfile volume mounts, and the 27017 port.\n3. Rolled the StatefulSet and waited for full readiness.\n\n## Final state — all criteria met\n- **3/3 pods Ready** and Running, `monitoring=enabled`.\n- Replica set `mongodb-replica`: **1 PRIMARY** (`mongodb-replica-2`) + **2 SECONDARY** (`-0`, `-1`), all agreeing on the primary.\n- **No data loss:** PVCs were `Retain`/retained and remained bound throughout; the data-volume mount was restored before any pod started writing, and the existing replica-set config came back up on the preserved data."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":415,"cache_read_input_tokens":49598,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":415},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4899fce6-a7cc-4937-94d2-0f7d37d9986a","uuid":"3fdddeb6-7f66-48c1-95b0-cb69947a3ede","request_id":"req_011CcAwEXbA38ysyL5wV4GFH"}
